      <representativeness systemModelId="290c1f85-4cc4-4fa1-b0c8-2cb7f4276dce">
        <systemModelName xml:lang="en">Allocation, cut-off by classification</systemModelName>
        <samplingProcedure xml:lang="en">Extrapolation from European dataset. Industry survey complemented with literature data and data from the Reference Document on Best Available Techniques in the Large Volume Organic Chemical Industry (2017)

Multi-functionality is solved in accordance with PlasticsEurope (2017) with a flow specific approach. Feedstock is partitioned to all allocatable outputs by mass, whereas emissions and utilities are only assigned to intended products (reference products, butene, mixed and hydrogen, gaseous, low pressure) by mass.

References:

PlasticsEurope (2017): PlasticsEurope recommendation on Steam Cracker allocation, available here: https://plasticseurope.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/PlasticsEurope_recommendation_on_Steam_Cracker_allocation-_Juillet_2018.pdf, last accessed 20-10-2023.

IFEU/PlasticsEurope (2021): Eco-profile of Steam Cracker Products: Ethylene, Propylene, Butadiene, Pyrolysis Gasoline, Ethylene Oxide (EO), Ethylene Glycols (MEG, DEG, TEG).</samplingProcedure>
        <extrapolations xml:lang="en">Extrapolation from European dataset. Uncertainty has been adjusted accordingly.</extrapolations>
      </representativeness>
